title: Correlation features of the reaction Be-9(d,pg)Be-10 at Ed=15.3 MeV and structure of the Be-10 nucleus.

x4freetext: Correlation features of the reaction Be-9(d,pg)Be-10 at
Ed=15.3 MeV and structure of the Be-10 nucleus.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physics of Atomic Nuclei, Vol.64, p.1909 (2001)

x4freetext: Four silicon detectors with the thickness of about
1000 mu-m and the energy resolution of 2.5 degrees.
These detectors were placed inside scattering chamber
on a special table which pitch relative to horizontal
plane could vary within pi/2. One detector was used to
measure the angle and energy dependences with the angle
resolution of 1 degree. This detector was placed on a
horizontal plane outside the scattering chamber.
with the angle resolution of 12 degrees. Gamma-
detectors were placed outside scattering chamber on a
horizontal rotational plane with an angle step of 32.5
The target was self-supporting Be-9 of 1-5 mg/cm2.
